    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>GWT does not directly support <code>&lt;input type='range' /&gt;</code> elements, but it has a generic <code>&lt;input /&gt;</code> element support: <a href=\"http://www.gwtproject.org/javadoc/latest/com/google/gwt/dom/client/InputElement.html\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\">InputElement</a>.</p>\n<p>You can <em>cast</em> your slider element to an InputElement this way:</p>\n<pre><code>InputElement input = InputElement.as(Document.get().getElementById(&quot;counter&quot;));\n</code></pre>\n<p>To get the value just call:</p>\n<pre><code>input.getValue();\n</code></pre>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
